dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Constanta, sheet R-53/54. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4375)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4375. Alternate title: Constanta, Romania. Transverse Mercator projection. Universal transverse Mercator and Danube zone grids. UTM grid added, gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1948. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With Romanian and Bulgarian glossaries. Intelligence reports up to 1942. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1948.
